The paper deals with the problem of sparse signal recovery, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), and signal processing (cs.SP). The paper also extends the approach to the temporally correlated multiple measurement vector (MMV) case, which falls under the category of multiple input multiple output (MIMO) systems, making cs.MM a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper uses an algorithm that leverages the convergence properties of GGAMP, which is a type of iterative algorithm commonly used in numerical analysis (cs.NA).
